g.text: The pktmbufpool is just a Mempool, where each buffer is an MBUF with structure and dataSizeof(pktmbuf_t) = 64 bytes or a cachelineHeadroom space (192 bytes)and used for prepending packet headersMempoolbuffers are fixed size, say 2048 bytes then subtract sizeof(pktmbuf_t) = 1984 bytes for packet dataPktmbufpools have a set of APIs to allocated/free mbufs/buffers to the mempooland initialize or clear mbuf metadata
Lockless Ring (Holds free buffers not in memcache)Size is total number of buffers in Mempool
